The paper proposes a new deep convolutional neural network architecture for semantic segmentation, which is a task in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on learning pixel embeddings, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves modifications to convolution routines, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
